根据[[BuzzFeed|BuzzFeed]]，在总统竞选活动的最后三个月中，Facebook上前20篇虚假的竞选相关文章中有17篇是反克林顿或亲特朗普的。Facebook用户与这些内容的互动相较来自真实新闻机构的报道更为频繁<ref name=CBSNews20161117>{{cite news|title=Probe reveals stunning stats about fake election headlines on Facebook|date=2016-11-17|publisher=[[CBS_News|CBS News]]|accessdate=2017-05-05|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/facebook-fake-election-news-more-popular-than-real-news-buzzfeed-investigation/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171223030232/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/facebook-fake-election-news-more-popular-than-real-news-buzzfeed-investigation/|archive-date=2017-12-23|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[美国总统|美国总统]][[唐納·川普|唐納·川普]]频繁使用「假新闻」一词称呼传统新闻媒体，其中单独针对[[CNN|CNN]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://insider.foxnews.com/2017/02/16/very-fake-news-trump-questioned-cnn-jim-acosta|title='Very Fake News': Pres. Trump Questioned on Intel Leaks by CNN's Acosta|date=2017-02-16|publisher=[[Fox_News|Fox News]]|access-date=2018-01-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180122032447/http://insider.foxnews.com/2017/02/16/very-fake-news-trump-questioned-cnn-jim-acosta|archive-date=2018-01-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>。语言学家[[喬治·萊考夫|喬治·萊考夫]]说这制造出了对该词的含义的困惑<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.npr.org/2017/02/17/515630467/with-fake-news-trump-moves-from-alternative-facts-to-alternative-language|title=With 'Fake News,' Trump Moves From Alternative Facts To Alternative Language|publisher=[[NPR|NPR]]|accessdate=2017-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171229101001/https://www.npr.org/2017/02/17/515630467/with-fake-news-trump-moves-from-alternative-facts-to-alternative-language|archive-date=2017-12-29|dead-url=no}}</ref>。根据CBS的《[[60分鐘時事雜誌|60分鐘時事雜誌]]》，特朗普总统可以使用假新闻一词称呼任何新闻，不论其是否是确切或负责的，只要他不同意新闻的内容<ref name=60Minutes />。

2016年12月，一位持枪的[[北卡罗来纳|北卡罗来纳]]男子——埃德加·麦迪逊·韦尔奇，前往[[华盛顿特区|华盛顿特区]]，并在Comet Ping Pong披萨店开枪，原因是受到一则{{link-en|披萨门阴谋论|Pizzagate conspiracy theory|指控民主党领导人在披萨店中运行一个恋童团伙}}的网上假新闻故事（美國媒體以「-{zh-hk:薄餅;zh-tw:比薩;zh-cn:披萨;zh-sg:披萨}-門」一詞稱之）驱使<ref name="auto3">{{Cite news|url=http://www.politifact.com/truth-o-meter/statements/2016/nov/04/conservative-daily-post/evidence-ridiculously-thin-sensational-claim-huge-/|title=Evidence ridiculously thin for Clinton sex network claim|publisher=[[PolitiFact.com|PolitiFact.com]]|accessdate=2017-01-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161201012633/http://www.politifact.com/truth-o-meter/statements/2016/nov/04/conservative-daily-post/evidence-ridiculously-thin-sensational-claim-huge-/|archive-date=2016-12-01|dead-url=no}}</ref>。这类故事倾向于迅速爆红。例如[[Facebook|Facebook]]的社交媒体网站，在假新闻的传播中起重要作用。这类系统展示给用户反映他们兴趣和浏览历史的内容，以致虚假或误导性的新闻。在与检察官[[认罪协商|认罪协商]]后，韦尔奇对跨州运输武器的联邦指控和使用危险武器袭击的哥伦比亚特区指控认罪。在2017年6月22日韦尔奇被判四年监禁并同意赔偿饭店损失了的5744.33[[美元|美元]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2017/06/22/533941689/pizzagate-gunman-sentenced-to-4-years-in-prison|title='Pizzagate' Gunman Sentenced To 4 Years in Prison|work=NPR.org|accessdate=2017-06-28|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170622193717/http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2017/06/22/533941689/pizzagate-gunman-sentenced-to-4-years-in-prison|archive-date=2017-06-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2016年底，媒體揭露在[[2016年美國總統選舉|2016年美國總統選舉]]期間，一些[[美國保守主義|美國保守主義]]網站上支持[[唐納·川普|唐納·川普]]的假新聞來自[[北馬其頓|北馬其頓]]小城[[韋萊斯|韋萊斯]]，因此該市又被稱為「假新聞樞紐」<ref>{{Cite news|title=The city getting rich from fake news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-38168281|work=BBC News|date=2016-12-05|access-date=2022-06-23|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Oxenham |first=Simon |date=2019-05-29|title=‘I was a Macedonian fake news writer’ |url=https://www.bbc.com/future/article/20190528-i-was-a-macedonian-fake-news-writer |website=www.bbc.com |language=en |access-date=2022-06-23}}</ref>。

